name: E. F. Kennedy, Constable of the Third District, Dade County, Florida, Plaintiff in Error, v. W Cecil Watson, Chairman, and J. D. Redd, C. H. Crandon, Hugh Peters, and R. P. Barfield, Members, constituting the Board of County Commissioners, in and for Dade County, Florida, Defendants in Error

judges: Terrell, C. J., and Whitfield, Strum and Brown, J. J., concur.
Ellis and Buford, J. J., dissent.
parties: E. F. Kennedy, Constable of the Third District, Dade County, Florida, Plaintiff in Error, v. W Cecil Watson, Chairman, and J. D. Redd, C. H. Crandon, Hugh Peters, and R. P. Barfield, Members, constituting the Board of County Commissioners, in and for Dade County, Florida, Defendants in Error.

opinions.text:
Per Curiam.
Affirmed on authority of Williams, et al., v. State ex rel., Newberger, filed this day.
Terrell, C. J., and Whitfield, Strum and Brown, J. J., concur.
Ellis and Buford, J. J., dissent.
opinions.author: Per Curiam.

opinions.text:
Buford, J.,
(dissenting) : I dissent adhering to the opinion prepared by me in Williams v. State filed at this term.
Ellis, J., concurs.
opinions.author: Buford, J.,

attorneys: Bart A. Riley, for Plaintiff in Error;
A. B. Small and Wallace Ruff, for Defendants in Error.
casebody.head_matter:
E. F. Kennedy, Constable of the Third District, Dade County, Florida, Plaintiff in Error, v. W Cecil Watson, Chairman, and J. D. Redd, C. H. Crandon, Hugh Peters, and R. P. Barfield, Members, constituting the Board of County Commissioners, in and for Dade County, Florida, Defendants in Error.
En Banc.
Decision filed December 20, 1930.
Bart A. Riley, for Plaintiff in Error;
A. B. Small and Wallace Ruff, for Defendants in Error.
